    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I fixed using a component with state and waiting the second `searching=true` event:\r\n\r\n```jsx\r\ngetInitialState () {\r\n    return {loading: true, ready: false}\r\n  },\r\n  \r\n  componentWillReceiveProps () {\r\n    const {props, state} = this\r\n    const {searching} = props\r\n    const {ready} = state\r\n    if (searching && !ready) this.setState({loading: false, ready: true})\r\n  },\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen in the component render method:\r\n\r\n```jsx\r\nconst {loading} = state\r\nconst render = loading ? renderLoader : renderResults\r\n```\r\n\r\nMaybe you are interested on include that in your code and emit a `ready` prop complementary to `searching`.",
